Please support one of my comedy heros @sinbadbad at WWW.TheJourneyForward.life He needs our help. This is how I met Sinbad. Don't be lazy, read it.

I met Sinbad around 1993 at Alabama State University while I was a student there. He was on a black college Coca-Cola tour. 

He completely rocked a packed auditorium full of young urban college kids without using a single curse word. I was a writer for the school newspaper at the time and he allowed me to interview him after the show. When we completed the interview, I told him that I was an aspiring comedian and was looking to move to LA after I finished college. I asked if he could help me in any way. 

He said in context; the best thing I could do is put myself in a position to be helped by becoming a strong stand up comedian and moving to LA. In addition, if he was ever in a position to do something for me, he would. 

Well, about four months after arriving to LA in 1995, I saw he was shooting a movie entitled "First Kid." I urged my manager to get me an audition for the movie, which she did. 

As God would have it, I made it to the call-back round and Sinbad was there reading with the actors. When he saw me, his face lit up. The producers decided to go with another actor for the part I auditioned for, but Sinbad told them the back story and insisted they create a part for me in the movie.

Shortly afterwards, he saw to it that not only they fly me into Virginia to work on the movie, but my sister, @jwalton511 ,to assist me as well. I only had a small part in the movie, but the experience for me and my sister was priceless. Here’s the picture we took between takes on the set. 

Sinbad is truly one of the best celebrities I have ever met. I will never forget his kindness and what he did for me and my sister as long as I live. Hang in there brother. We love you!!! Swipe 👈🏽.
